document_data.mainbody:
Traders Way was a prominent road that was located in the city of Waterdeep.
Traders Way originated on Julthoon Street at the border of the Dock Ward and Sea Ward. It branched southeast then east, passed by the north side of the Market, then merged with the High Road on the far east side of the Market at a large intersection that also included Bazaar Street and Suldown Street. Other roads connectin with Traders Way included Gothal Street, Melshars Street, Tchozals Race, the Sutherlane, Mendever Street, Sul Street, Shield Street, and Copper Street.
